This paper is primarily focused on image analysis and synthesis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of variational capsules also involves probabilistic modeling and deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the disentanglement of semantic attributes, which is a topic often studied in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
